peg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221445%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDarrin%20Lowery%20found%20nearly%20300%20artifacts%20on%20Parsons%20Islands%2C%20some%20of%20which%20he%20dated%20to%20around%2022%2C000%20years%20old.%3Cp%3EDarrin%20Lowery%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%20something%20significant%20was%20happening%20across%20northern%20North%20America%3A%20The%20glaciers%20that%20had%20covered%20part%20of%20the%20continent%20for%20millennia%20were%20melting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArchaeologists%20thought%20humans%20needed%20to%20wait%20for%20those%20glaciers%20to%20melt%20to%20migrate%20across%20this%20region.%20Otherwise%2C%20the%20journey%20through%20what%20is%20now%20Canada%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.neh.gov%2Fhumanities%2F2014%2Fmarchapril%2Ffeature%2Fthe-first-americans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20too%20dangerous%2C%20with%20little%20food%20available%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20for%20most%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20theory%20was%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20first%20Americans%20came%20from%20Asia%20around%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20crossing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextinct-giant-mammals-pleistocene-megafauna-ice-age-north-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow-submerged%3C%2Fa%3E%20Bering%20land%20bridge%20that%20connected%20Siberia%20and%20present-day%20Alaska.%20Then%20those%20humans%20and%20their%20ancestors%20made%20their%20way%20across%20the%20areas%20of%20the%20Americas%20with%20fewer%20glaciers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20older%20sites%20were%20turning%20up%2C%20like%20a%2014%2C500-year-old%20site%20in%20Chile%2C%20Monte%20Verde.%20If%20people%20were%20that%20far%20south%20at%20the%20time%2C%20it%20meant%20humans%20had%20to%20have%20traveled%20from%20North%20America%20to%20South%20America%20well%20before%2013%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20changed%20everything%20about%20what%20we%20understood%20about%20when%20and%20how%20people%20arrived%20to%20the%20Americas%2C%26quot%3B%20Braje%20said%20of%20the%20Chile%20site.%20One%20alternative%20theory%20is%20that%20people%20followed%20the%20less%20icy%20Pacific%20Coast%20and%20then%20started%20moving%20east.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20individual%20sites%20are%20often%20subjects%20of%20debate%2C%20the%20widely%20accepted%20range%20of%20humans'%20first%20arrival%20in%20the%20Americas%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20now%20between%2020%2C000%20to%2015%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20Braje%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELowery%20said%20his%20artifacts%20are%20even%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226c255e81-c76d-4200-899f-0ef2ae0d71f2%5C%22%3EDating%2022%2C000-year-old%20artifacts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224896%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20embankment%20on%20Parsons%20Island%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664fc9ad20abc1efe8fd3802%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EParsons%20Island%20has%20undergone%20a%20lot%20of%20erosion%2C%20so%20many%20of%20the%20artifacts%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20their%20original%20location.%3Cp%3EDarrin%20Lowery%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%2093%20visits%20to%20Parsons%20Island%2C%20Lowery%20and%20other%20volunteers%20found%20a%20mix%20of%20chipped-off%20rock%20flakes%2C%20a%20stone%20for%20hammering%2C%20and%20knives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20erosion%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.udel.edu%2Fudaily%2F2020%2Fnovember%2Fresearching-parsons-island-geology-archeology%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20artifacts%20fell%20out%20of%20the%20embankment%20that%20once%20held%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enine%20were%20still%20stuck%20in%20the%20bank%2C%20and%20three%20of%20those%20dated%20to%20around%2022%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDating%20ancient%20artifacts%20like%20this%20is%20tricky%20and%20is%20often%20the%20source%20of%20contention%20around%20these%20sites%20that%20question%20our%20understanding%20and%20timeline%20of%20ancient%20human%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20most%20dating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uwlax.edu%2Fmvac%2Fprocess-of-archaeology%2Flab-analysis%2Fdating%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emethods%3C%2Fa%3E%20require%20organic%20material%20and%20won't%20work%20on%20stone%20tools.%20Instead%2C%20scientists%20test%20charcoal%2C%20pollen%2C%20and%20other%20matter%20found%20near%20stone%20artifacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20a%20tool%20shifts%20from%20its%20original%20position%20%E2%80%94%20like%20if%20it%20falls%20out%20of%20the%20embankment%20that's%20holding%20it%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20difficult%20to%20date%20it%20reliably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20Lowery's%20artifacts%20could%20be%20tested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Lowery%20doesn't%20want%20to%20publish%20a%20paper%20through%20peer%20review%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bantiquated%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20he%20did%20his%20due%20diligence%20in%20dating%20the%20artifacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20used%20different%20methods%20to%20date%20the%20still-in-place%20artifacts%20and%20also%20sent%20samples%20to%20independent%20labs%20for%20verification.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20radiocarbon%20dating%20that%20measured%20the%20amount%20of%20carbon%20in%20flakes%20of%20charcoal%2C%20an%20independent%20lab%20estimated%20the%20artifacts'%20ages%20to%20be%20between%2020%2C563%20and%2022%2C656%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20these%20artifacts%20are%20as%20old%20as%20the%20lab%20analysis%20suggests%2C%20then%20Lowery's%20discovery%20could%20rewrite%20our%20understanding%20of%20ancient%20American%20human%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7c9b503-d71f-4677-85e8-23800441c203%5C%22%3EThe%20journey%20from%20Alaska%20to%20Maryland%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20North%20America%20covered%20in%20large%20glaciers%2021%2C000%20years%20ago%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66574ed8d0b8e1c832c9c447%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221495%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAround%2021%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20glaciers%20covered%20most%20of%20Canada.%3Cp%3ENOAA%20Climate.gov%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2021%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fccin.ca%2Findex.php%2Fccw%2Fglaciers%2Fpast%2Fglaciation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20of%20Canada%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelicopter-tours-canada-glacier-melt-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecovered%20in%20glaciers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Therefore%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20questions%20with%20Lowery's%20theory%20is%20how%20humans%20could%20have%20made%20the%20trek%20from%20Alaska%20to%20Maryland%2022%2C000%20years%20ago%20when%20there%20was%20a%20vast%2C%20icy%20landscape%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Lowery%20said%20nearly%2026%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-ancient-intact-wolf-pup-mummy-yukon-permafrost-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeringian%20wolves%3C%2Fa%3E%20traveled%20through%20a%20temporary%20corridor%20between%20ice%20sheets.%20Humans%20could%20have%20used%20the%20same%20route%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20largely%20a%20misconception%20that%20ice%20is%20an%20impediment%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowery%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20challenge%2C%20but%20humans%20are%20pretty%20damn%20smart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELowery%20admitted%20this%20is%20just%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20one%20som