mes.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDraw%20a%20rough%20sketch%20of%20the%20theme%20of%20your%20garden%20in%20mind%20and%20select%20a%20suitable%20tray%20based%20on%20its%20size%2C%20shape%2C%20and%20material%20like%20mud%20and%20ceramic.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFill%20the%20tray%20with%20potting%20mix%20to%20create%20a%20base%20for%20your%20garden.%20Mix%2050%20percent%20of%20fertile%20soil%20with%2015%20percent%20cow%20dung%2C%2015%20percent%20cocopeat%2C%20and%2010%20percent%20perlite%20and%20bone%20meal%20each.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPlant%20small%20and%20dwarf%20varieties%20of%20plants%20like%20succulents%2C%20snake%20plants%2C%20syngonium%2C%20jade%20and%20spider%20plants.%20Water%20it%20and%20press%20the%20soil%20from%20above%20to%20let%20it%20settle.%20It%20takes%20roughly%20an%20hour%20to%20settle%20the%20soil%20in%20summer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELater%20on%2C%20build%20your%20pathways%2C%20huts%2C%20or%20other%20structures.%20Decorate%20your%20garden%20with%20colourful%20pebbles%2C%20hedges%2C%20bells%2C%20dolls%2C%20and%20other%20decorative%20items.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWater%20the%20tray%20using%20a%20spray%20bottle%2C%20carefully.%20You%20can%20also%20spray%20liquid%20compost%20using%20kitchen%20waste%20like%20banana%2C%20garlic%2C%20ginger%2C%20and%20onion%20peels%20to%20fertilise%20soil%20and%20prevent%20the%20plant%20from%20fungal%20attacks.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETo%20make%20the%20compost%2C%20collect%20peels%20in%20a%20bucket%20and%20add%20some%20water%20to%20it.%20After%20two%20to%20three%20days%2C%20strain%20the%20contents%20and%20mix%20it%20with%20clean%20water%20in%20a%20ratio%20of%201%3A2.%20Spray%20this%20fertiliser%20on%20all%20tray%20gardens%20every%20two%20to%20three%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharda%20says%20it%20takes%20her%20roughly%2020%20minutes%20to%20decorate%20the%20tray%20garden.%20%E2%80%9CWhenever%20I%20get%20bored%2C%20I%20recreate%20these%20tray%20gardens%20using%20the%20same%20plant